<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-03-05</DATELINE><TITLE>COVID-19 and the cardiovascular system</TITLE><BODY>Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2) infects host cells through ACE2 receptors, leading to coronavirus disease (COVID-19)-related pneumonia, while also causing acute myocardial injury and chronic damage to the cardiovascular system. Therefore, particular attention should be given to cardiovascular protection during treatment for COVID-19.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>